---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>AI for Nursing Practice and Learning</h1>
			<p>
				Welcome to <strong>Nurse AI Notes</strong>, a practical blog for student nurses, new graduates,
				clinical educators, and experienced nurses who want to use artificial intelligence safely and
				effectively.
			</p>
			<p>
				Each article translates AI concepts into bedside-relevant decisions: how to evaluate clinical
				tools, improve study workflows, protect patient privacy, and communicate clearly with
				interprofessional teams.
			</p>
			<p>What you will find here:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>AI explainers for medication safety, triage, charting, and patient education.</li>
				<li>Study support ideas for NCLEX prep, concept mapping, and clinical reflection.</li>
				<li>Workflow tips for documentation quality, handoff communication, and time management.</li>
				<li>Ethics guidance on bias, accountability, and responsible AI use in nursing care.</li>
				<li>Implementation checklists for nurse leaders and quality improvement teams.</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				Start with the latest post in the <a href="/blog">blog archive</a>, then explore the About page
				for this site's editorial focus and evidence standards.
			</p>
			<p>
				This site is educational content and not a substitute for institutional policy, clinical
				judgment, or patient-specific medical advice.
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
